CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper June 23, 1956, pg. 1, reads: "New Vice Chairman - Fifth Ward Democratic Committee officials show their pleasure over their new vice chairman, Mrs. Lula Hatcher, third from left, who won over Mrs. Louise Russell, 45-3, in Tuesday's election at Leo Weil School. Extending congratulation are, left to right, Fifth Ward Alderman Harry B. Fitzgerald, Ward Chairman Robert E. (Pappy) Williams, Mrs. Hatcher, Prothonotary David B. Roberts, Fifth Ward Constable Thomas J. Smith, and State Representative Matt S. Anderson, who was elected secretary. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Fifth Ward Alderman Harry B. Fitzgerald shaking hands with Democratic Committee Vice Chairman Lula Hatcher, with Ward Chairman Robert E. "Pappy" Williams between them, Prothonotary David B. Roberts, Constable Thomas J. "Tommy" Smith, and Pennsylvania State Representative Matt S. Anderson standing in A. Leo Weil School
